# TimeTiles — Privacy Policy

**Last updated: April 2026**

## Overview

TimeTiles is a Chrome extension that displays the current time across Ellen MacArthur Foundation office locations and provides a time zone converter. This policy explains how the extension handles your data.

## Data collection

TimeTiles does **not** collect, store, transmit or share any personal data with third parties.

## How it works

- All time calculations happen locally in your browser using the JavaScript `Intl` API
- No external API calls are made — no data leaves your device
- If you grant location permission, your coordinates are used locally to detect which office you are nearest to. Your location is never stored or transmitted.
- Your location is only requested at the moment you open the extension and is not retained between sessions

## Permissions

| Permission | Reason |
|---|---|
| `storage` | To store user preferences locally |
| `sidePanel` | To display TimeTiles as a browser side panel |
| `geolocation` | To detect which EMF office you are nearest to. Optional — the extension works without it. |

